claim.claim-text:
1. A system containing a plurality of gyroscopes, each gyroscope operating at a different natural frequency (ωR), each gyroscope in the system comprising:
a mixer receiving output signals from a gyroscope at the natural frequency of operation (ωR) and reference signals at a frequency (ωLO) that is the sum of the natural frequency of operation ωR) of the gyroscope and a predetermined operating frequency for the system, the mixer combining the signals from the gyroscope (ωR) with the reference signals ωLO to form a signal (ωIF) having a (ωLO+ωR) and a (ωLO−ωR) component;
a filter receiving the components of the signal (ωIF) and removing the (ωLO+ωR) component leaving the (ωLO−ωR) component signals at the predetermined operating frequency for the system;
a phase lock loop receiving a system clock signal and the (ωLO−ωR) component signals and generating the reference signals at a frequency (ωLO); and
a data processor receiving the (ωLO−ωR) component signals from the filter at the operating frequency of the system and processing the received signals at the system operating frequency to generate a directional signal.

5. A method for controlling a plurality of gyroscopes operating together in a system, the steps of the method comprising:
determining an operating frequency for all the gyroscopes in the system;
measuring natural frequency of an output signal from a first gyroscope;
determining a first reference signal by summing the first measured natural frequency and the determined operating frequency;
combining the first reference signal with an output signal from the first gyroscope to form a signal from the first gyroscope having the operating frequency;
measuring the natural frequency of an output signal from a second gyroscope;
determining a second reference signal by summing the second measured natural frequency and the determined operating frequency; and
combining the second reference signal with an output signal from the second gyroscope to form a signal from the second gyroscope having the operating frequency.
